column19: First mobile Quadro based on the Geforce2 Go, Dynamic core clock 100–143 MHz, Dynamic Voltage 1.575V, graphics core listed as 64-bit and 128-bit for DDR and SDR SDRAM types respectively according to Nvidia [166][167]
Based on the Geforce4 Go, dynamic core clock 66–220 MHz, core voltage 1.35 V, uses DDR SDRAM according to Nvidia brochures[167]
Based on Geforce4 Go 4200, uses DDR according to Nvidia brochures
Based on the Geforce FX Go 5 (FX 56XX), uses DDR SDRAM.

Last chip designated as a Quadro FX Go, apparently uses PCIE instead of AGP 8×. Core config has been mentioned as either 8:5:8:8 or 12:5:12:12 - the latter is likely since chip is derived from Geforce Go 6800.
